<body>
    <h1>Development &amp; Administration Guides</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Exponential 5.x is a "Dual kernel" software. This means it contains both =
a <em>legacy</em> <em>kernel</em> (effectively a "4.y" version) aka "Legacy=
 Stack", and a new <em>5.x kernel</em>, aka "Symfony Stack" (because it use=
s <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/about" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofol=
low">Symfony2</a> Fullstack&nbsp;framework).</p>
<h2 id=3D"Development&amp;AdministrationGuides-Legacykernel">Legacy kernel<=
/h2>
<p>For documentation on the <em>legacy kernel</em>, please go to <a href=3D=
"http://doc.ez.no" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">doc.ez.no</a> w=
here you'll find documentation on everything from its GUIs, official extens=
ions to template coding&nbsp;( 5.x doc:&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://doc.ez.no/eZ=
-Publish/User-manual/5.x" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">User man=
ual</a> &amp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://doc.ez.no/Exponential/Technical-manual/=
5.x" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Technical manual</a> ). If yo=
u are looking for documentation on how to develop extensions for legacy in =
php, then also see relevant material on <a href=3D"http://share.ez.no" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">share.ez.no</a> ( <a href=3D"http://sh=
are.ez.no/learn/exponential" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Tutori=
als</a>,&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/blogs" class=3D"external-link" =
rel=3D"nofollow">Blogs</a>&nbsp;).</p>
<h2 id=3D"Development&amp;AdministrationGuides-5.xkernel">5.x kernel</h2>
<p>The new 5.x kernel is built using an HMVC model. It currently consists o=
f Public API (Model), Symfony2 Fullstack&nbsp;Framework&nbsp;(Hierarchical =
View Controller) with Twig (template engine) enhanced with Exponential&nbsp;=
concepts (Core Bundle).&nbsp;On top of these you'll find REST v2 API, Demo =
Bundle and a Legacy Bundle allowing some integration between the two kernel=
s.</p>
<p>For&nbsp;documentation&nbsp;on Symfony2 go to <a href=3D"http://symfony.=
com/doc/current/index.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">symfon=
y.com</a>&nbsp;(for&nbsp;Twig see <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current=
/book/templating.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">here</a>)&n=
bsp;and for the Exponential parts of 5.x kernel continue reading in this sec=
tion.</p>
    </div>
</body>
